description:
Peter Milligan's reimagining of classic Greek myths set in modern-day London comes to a shocking conclusion with a deus ex machina like you've never seen before. Collecting issues #12-16.

Back Blurb

Gods and monsters

The old stories still hold sway on Greek Street. And none are older -- or more powerful -- than stories of love and war.

Alex is home safe from a deadly tour in Afghanistan. Instead of the medal he deserves, he brought home only a bad leg -- and psychic wounds far more difficult to heal. Can he put the ghosts of war behind him, or will he turn London's streets into a battlefield?

Meanwhile, the monstrous murderess called Medea has earned the wrath of Greek Street's underworld overlords. The only way she can survive their vengeance is by unlocking the love that still lives deep inside her heart -- and inside Eddie, the desperate man sent to end her reign of terror.

But above it all, the true authors of all the drama and tragedy Greek Street has seen are about to make themselves known. And they demand adoration... and sacrifice...

Acclaimed writer Peter Milligan (HELLBLAZER) and artists Werther Dell'Edera (LOVELESS) and Davide Gianfelice (NORTHLANDERS) proudly present GREEK STREET: MEDEA'S LUCK, the final act of their very modern take on the classic tales that gave bloody birth to so-called civilization.
